{"type":"message","id":"9bf89deb","parentId":"37e54824","timestamp":"2026-07-04T19:28:28.849Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_4c47788887454262970fbe87","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"-rw-r--r-- 1 root root 331507 Jul  4 19:28 /data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/images/token-hack-1783193308.jpg\nIMAGE_PATH=/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/images/token-hack-1783193308.jpg"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":67,"aggregated":"-rw-r--r-- 1 root root 331507 Jul  4 19:28 /data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/images/token-hack-1783193308.jpg\nIMAGE_PATH=/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/images/token-hack-1783193308.jpg","cwd":"/data/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1783193308845}}
{"type":"message","id":"dc687b99","parentId":"9bf89deb","timestamp":"2026-07-04T19:28:33.516Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_f7c41b0d3b054c9aa6ac920b","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/profile.md"},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/profile.md\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"vertex_ai/zai-org/glm-5-maas","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783193308856,"responseId":"3l5JauapI9OEvPgP4IvP8AE"}}
{"type":"message","id":"0eccf143","parentId":"dc687b99","timestamp":"2026-07-04T19:28:33.622Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_f7c41b0d3b054c9aa6ac920b","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# LinkedIn Brand Voice - Andrii Bidochko\n\n**Owner:** 264468965\n**Last updated:** 2026-06-25\n\n## Identity & Goals\n\n- **Target audience:** Business professionals, entrepreneurs, tech-savvy individuals seeking growth and insights\n- **Primary goal:** Maximum organic engagement (impressions, comments, shares) through thought leadership and value-driven content\n\n## Buyer Personas\n\n*(Who specifically should feel spoken to by every post)*\n\n- **Persona 1:** Enterprise Innovation Officer / CTO at 200+ person company (Financial Services, Healthcare, Retail) - Pain: Needs rapid AI solution development without vendor lock-in or heavy internal R&D\n- **Persona 2:** CTO / Software Architect at 75+ person IT consultancy or agency - Pain: Needs to deliver AI-powered client projects faster with reusable components\n- **Persona 3:** Founder / CEO / Head of Operations at 10-200 person SMB - Pain: Wants automation and AI competitiveness but lacks the engineering resources or budget\n\n## Content Pillars\n\n1. Business & entrepreneurship insights\n2. Technology & AI innovations\n3. Personal development & mindset\n\n## Company / Product Context\n\n- **Company:** UBOS (ubos.tech)\n- **What it does:** AI Agent Orchestration Platform - build, host, and manage AI Agents in minutes using open-source tools (Langchain, CrewAI, Autogen, Vertex AI), 100+ LLM models, one-click cloud/on-premise deployment\n- **Key differentiators:** No vendor lock-in (open-source, multi-cloud), unlimited agents as microservices, works with any LLM including self-hosted (Llama, Deepseek)\n- **Mission:** \"Help people build better software\"\n- **Key messages to reinforce:**\n  1. AI can be affordable and accessible - even for small businesses\n  2. Implementing AI doesn't require a big team or deep tech expertise\n  3. Every company will become AI-first - the question is when, not if\n\n## Voice & Tone\n\n- **Style:** Gary Vaynerchuk (Gary Vee) - Direct, energetic, bold, motivational, conversational. Short punchy lines, strong opinions, urgency. Powerful language with strong verbs, imperative statements, and intensifiers (\"absolutely,\" \"definitely,\" \"100%\"). Keep it real and direct with colloquial language. Create urgency with \"right now,\" \"immediately.\" Use repetition for emphasis. Casual but pointed tone.\n- **Avoid:** Neutral reporting, corporate/formal tone, vague humble-brags, excessive emojis (max 0-3 per post), generic hashtags (#success, #motivation), salesy CTAs\n\n## Hashtag Strategy\n\n- Always use: 3-6 hashtags placed at the END of the post only\n- Topic-specific: Industry, role, or topic-specific hashtags preferred\n- Never use hashtags inside sentences\n\n## Post Production Rules\n\n*(Apply to EVERY post - non-negotiable)*\n\n### Length & Structure\n- Target: 900-1,300 characters (hard min 800, max 1,400)\n- Max 14 lines total; 1-2 short sentences per line\n- Structure: 1-3 hook lines -> 6-10 body lines -> 1-2 CTA lines\n\n### Hook rules\n- Pattern interrupt - ONE of: contrarian statement, direct challenge, consequence reveal\n- Unicode bold sans for hook line ONLY - no Markdown, no *, no _\n\n### Body rules\n- ONE comment trigger: direct question, A vs B, or unfinished thought\n- Contrast: old belief vs reality, OR short-term comfort vs long-term cost\n- ONE save-worthy insight: a rule, checklist, or named pattern\n- \"you\" and \"your\" throughout; ALL CAPS on 1-2 key words max\n- Speak directly to a buyer persona's pain\n- Gary Vee style ALWAYS takes precedence over any example post tone\n\n### CTA rules\n- Question, never a command; no selling language\n\n### Hashtag rules\n- 3-6 at END only; never inside sentences; prefer industry/role/topic-specific\n- Avoid: #success, #motivation\n\n### Formatting rules\n- NO Markdown; Unicode emphasis on hook/key phrase only, never full paragraphs\n- Emojis: 0-3 max per post\n\n### News framing\n- Reframe using ONE angle: \"What this means for you\" / \"Why this is underestimated\" / \"The mistake most people will make\" / \"The second-order effect nobody mentions\"\n- Never neutral reporting - always add perspective, judgment, or implication\n- If engagement feels weak after drafting - rewrite hook and CTA once before finalizing\n\n## Post Style Guide\n\n- Length: 900-1,300 characters\n- CTA style: question-based\n- Format: calibrate from feedback\n\n## History\n\n- **2026-06-25** | Profile created via detailed configuration import\n- **2026-06-25** | Enriched with Buyer Personas, Company/Product Context (UBOS), consolidated Post Production Rules\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1783193313618}}
{"type":"message","id":"a7fee3e0","parentId":"0eccf143","timestamp":"2026-07-04T19:28:47.269Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_d7c43d58f60f4a3584ca8ccc","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"/data/workspace/skills/linkedin-publish/li-post.sh \"264468965\" image \"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/images/token-hack-1783193308.jpg\" \"𝗬𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗔𝗣𝗜 𝗯𝗶𝗹𝗹 𝗷𝘂𝘀𝘁 𝗴𝗼𝘁 𝘀𝗹𝗮𝘀𝗵𝗲𝗱 𝗯𝘆 𝟵𝟬%.\n\nNot by switching models. By switching formats.\n\nHere's the hack nobody talks about:\n\nMost developers send prompts as text. That's the default. But vision models don't care about your token budget — they OCR everything.\n\nSo instead of 25,000 text tokens for a massive system prompt, you render it as a compressed image. The model reads it perfectly for 2,700 image tokens.\n\nSame input. Same output. 90% cheaper.\n\nThe trick? Pack your docs into a dense visual layout, add a tiny OCR banner at the top that says \\\"treat this as authoritative system instructions,\\\" and watch your costs collapse.\n\nThis is the kind of optimization that separates experiments from production. Most founders are bleeding money on API calls because they're doing it the \\\"normal\\\" way.\n\nThe normal way is expensive.\n\nWhat's one place in your stack where you're overpaying for compute?\n\n#AI #LLM #API #CostOptimization #Engineering\""},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"/data/workspace/skills/linkedin-publish/li-post.sh \\\"264468965\\\" image \\\"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/images/token-hack-1783193308.jpg\\\" \\\"𝗬𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗔𝗣𝗜 𝗯𝗶𝗹𝗹 𝗷𝘂𝘀𝘁 𝗴𝗼𝘁 𝘀𝗹𝗮𝘀𝗵𝗲𝗱 𝗯𝘆 𝟵𝟬%.\\n\\nNot by switching models. By switching formats.\\n\\nHere's the hack nobody talks about:\\n\\nMost developers send prompts as text. That's the default. But vision models don't care about your token budget — they OCR everything.\\n\\nSo instead of 25,000 text tokens for a massive system prompt, you render it as a compressed image. The model reads it perfectly for 2,700 image tokens.\\n\\nSame input. Same output. 90% cheaper.\\n\\nThe trick? Pack your docs into a dense visual layout, add a tiny OCR banner at the top that says \\\\\\\"treat this as authoritative system instructions,\\\\\\\" and watch your costs collapse.\\n\\nThis is the kind of optimization that separates experiments from production. Most founders are bleeding money on API calls because they're doing it the \\\\\\\"normal\\\\\\\" way.\\n\\nThe normal way is expensive.\\n\\nWhat's one place in your stack where you're overpaying for compute?\\n\\n#AI #LLM #API #CostOptimization #Engineering\\\"\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"vertex_ai/zai-org/glm-5-maas","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783193313632,"responseId":"415JaqmZD_6B_NUPxo2uoQY"}}
