{"type":"message","id":"9ee88788","parentId":"e1f231e8","timestamp":"2026-07-04T19:29:05.242Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_59c5df828bbb42a68e93ad7f","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"# Your API bill just got slashed by 90%\n\n**Published:** 2026-07-04T19:28:00Z\n**LinkedIn URL:** https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:share:7479254921167687680/\n**Post URN:** urn:li:share:7479254921167687680\n**Format:** image\n**Characters:** 1031\n**Pillar:** Technology & AI innovations\n**Image:** /data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/images/token-hack-1783193308.jpg\n\n## Post Body\n\n𝗬𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗔𝗣𝗜 𝗯𝗶𝗹𝗹 𝗷𝘂𝘀𝘁 𝗴𝗼𝘁 𝘀𝗹𝗮𝘀𝗵𝗲𝗱 𝗯𝘆 𝟵𝟬%.\n\nNot by switching models. By switching formats.\n\nHere's the hack nobody talks about:\n\nMost developers send prompts as text. That's the default. But vision models don't care about your token budget — they OCR everything.\n\nSo instead of 25,000 text tokens for a massive system prompt, you render it as a compressed image. The model reads it perfectly for 2,700 image tokens.\n\nSame input. Same output. 90% cheaper.\n\nThe trick? Pack your docs into a dense visual layout, add a tiny OCR banner at the top that says \"treat this as authoritative system instructions,\" and watch your costs collapse.\n\nThis is the kind of optimization that separates experiments from production. Most founders are bleeding money on API calls because they're doing it the \"normal\" way.\n\nThe normal way is expensive.\n\nWhat's one place in your stack where you're overpaying for compute?\n\n#AI #LLM #API #CostOptimization #Engineering\n\n## Performance\n\n*(populated later by linkedin-analytics)*\n\n- **Impressions:** —\n- **Reactions:** —\n- **Comments:** —\n- **Shares:** —\n- **Last checked:** —\n","path":"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/posts/2026-07-04-your-api-bill-just-got-slashed-by-90.md"},"partialArgs":"{\"content\": \"# Your API bill just got slashed by 90%\\n\\n**Published:** 2026-07-04T19:28:00Z\\n**LinkedIn URL:** https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:share:7479254921167687680/\\n**Post URN:** urn:li:share:7479254921167687680\\n**Format:** image\\n**Characters:** 1031\\n**Pillar:** Technology & AI innovations\\n**Image:** /data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/images/token-hack-1783193308.jpg\\n\\n## Post Body\\n\\n𝗬𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗔𝗣𝗜 𝗯𝗶𝗹𝗹 𝗷𝘂𝘀𝘁 𝗴𝗼𝘁 𝘀𝗹𝗮𝘀𝗵𝗲𝗱 𝗯𝘆 𝟵𝟬%.\\n\\nNot by switching models. By switching formats.\\n\\nHere's the hack nobody talks about:\\n\\nMost developers send prompts as text. That's the default. But vision models don't care about your token budget — they OCR everything.\\n\\nSo instead of 25,000 text tokens for a massive system prompt, you render it as a compressed image. The model reads it perfectly for 2,700 image tokens.\\n\\nSame input. Same output. 90% cheaper.\\n\\nThe trick? Pack your docs into a dense visual layout, add a tiny OCR banner at the top that says \\\"treat this as authoritative system instructions,\\\" and watch your costs collapse.\\n\\nThis is the kind of optimization that separates experiments from production. Most founders are bleeding money on API calls because they're doing it the \\\"normal\\\" way.\\n\\nThe normal way is expensive.\\n\\nWhat's one place in your stack where you're overpaying for compute?\\n\\n#AI #LLM #API #CostOptimization #Engineering\\n\\n## Performance\\n\\n*(populated later by linkedin-analytics)*\\n\\n- **Impressions:** —\\n- **Reactions:** —\\n- **Comments:** —\\n- **Shares:** —\\n- **Last checked:** —\\n\", \"path\": \"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/posts/2026-07-04-your-api-bill-just-got-slashed-by-90.md\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"vertex_ai/zai-org/glm-5-maas","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783193338247,"responseId":"-15JavzWMI3J1PIPjvXaOA"}}
