{"type":"message","id":"1d260ab7","parentId":"96c914e4","timestamp":"2026-07-05T06:14:25.161Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_47cb8d7352de4268bc63bcb1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"UID=\"264468965\"\nTODAY=$(date +%Y-%m-%d)\nPENDING_DIR=\"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/$UID/pending\"\nmkdir -p \"$PENDING_DIR\"\n\n# Draft 1\ncat > \"$PENDING_DIR/${TODAY}-draft-1.md\" << 'DRAFT_EOF'\n---\ndate: 2026-07-05\nn: 1\npillar: Technology & AI innovations\nsource: evergreen\nsource_date: 2026-07-05\nstatus: pending\n---\n\n𝗧𝗵𝗲 𝗔𝗜 𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝗿𝗮𝗰𝗲 𝗶𝘀𝗻'𝘁 𝗮𝗯𝗼𝘂𝘁 𝘄𝗵𝗼 𝗵𝗮𝘀 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗯𝗲𝘀𝘁 𝗺𝗼𝗱𝗲𝗹.\n\nIt's about who ships first.\n\nEvery week there's a new model. Smarter. Faster. Cheaper. And companies are frozen — waiting for the perfect stack, the perfect agent architecture, the perfect use case.\n\nMeanwhile, the winners are already in production with \"good enough\" agents solving real problems. They'll swap models later. The infrastructure stays. The learnings compound.\n\nThe gap between companies talking about AI and companies deploying AI is getting embarrassing. One group is writing strategy decks. The other is capturing market share.\n\nYour competitor's agent doesn't need to be perfect. It just needs to be live.\n\nWhat's stopping you from deploying your first agent this week?\n\n#AI #AIAgents #Innovation #Execution #UBOS\nDRAFT_EOF\n\necho \"SAVED: Draft 1\"\n\n# Draft 2\ncat > \"$PENDING_DIR/${TODAY}-draft-2.md\" << 'DRAFT_EOF'\n---\ndate: 2026-07-05\nn: 2\npillar: Business & entrepreneurship insights\nsource: evergreen\nsource_date: 2026-07-05\nstatus: pending\n---\n\n𝗬𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗻𝗲𝘁𝘄𝗼𝗿𝗸 𝗶𝘀 𝘆𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗯𝗲𝘀𝘁 𝗱𝗶𝘀𝘁𝗿𝗶𝗯𝘂𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻 𝗰𝗵𝗮𝗻𝗻𝗲𝗹.\n\nAnd you're ignoring it.\n\nFounders spend months chasing cold outreach, paid ads, and viral content. All valid. But the warmest leads are already in your phone — people who've seen you work, trust your judgment, and would take your call.\n\nThe problem? Most people only reach out when they need something. That's not networking. That's extracting.\n\nReal network building is:\n- Sharing wins without asking\n- Making intros without expecting returns\n- Commenting thoughtfully on posts\n- Showing up consistently in their feed\n\nBuild the relationship before you need the favor. By the time you launch, half the work is done.\n\nWho's one person in your network you should reconnect with this week?\n\n#Networking #FounderLife #Distribution #Relationships #Growth\nDRAFT_EOF\n\necho \"SAVED: Draft 2\"\n\n# Draft 3\ncat > \"$PENDING_DIR/${TODAY}-draft-3.md\" << 'DRAFT_EOF'\n---\ndate: 2026-07-05\nn: 3\npillar: Personal development & mindset\nsource: evergreen\nsource_date: 2026-07-05\nstatus: pending\n---\n\n𝗖𝗼𝗻𝘀𝗶𝘀𝘁𝗲𝗻𝗰𝘆 𝗯𝗲𝗮𝘁𝘀 𝗶𝗻𝘁𝗲𝗻𝘀𝗶𝘁𝘆 𝗲𝘃𝗲𝗿𝘆 𝘁𝗶𝗺𝗲.\n\nBut we keep betting on intensity.\n\nThe 14-hour sprint. The weekend warrior. The January 1st resolution. All gas, no steering. And then we burn out, disappear for months, and start over.\n\nThe people who win aren't the ones who go hardest. They're the ones who keep going.\n\n- Two posts a week, every week, beats ten posts one week and zero the next\n- 30 minutes of focus daily beats three hours on Sunday\n- One meaningful conversation a day beats ten networking events a year\n\nThe math is brutal: show up 1% better every day and you're 37x better in a year. Skip three months and you're at zero.\n\nYour brand, your skills, your network — they compound. But only if you keep adding to them.\n\nWhat's one thing you can commit to doing every day this month?\n\n#Mindset #Consistency #Growth #PersonalDevelopment #Habits\nDRAFT_EOF\n\necho \"SAVED: Draft 3\"\n\n# Mark brief as sent\ntouch \"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/$UID/pending/.brief-sent-$TODAY\"\necho \"Brief marked as sent for $TODAY\""},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"UID=\\\"264468965\\\"\\nTODAY=$(date +%Y-%m-%d)\\nPENDING_DIR=\\\"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/$UID/pending\\\"\\nmkdir -p \\\"$PENDING_DIR\\\"\\n\\n# Draft 1\\ncat > \\\"$PENDING_DIR/${TODAY}-draft-1.md\\\" << 'DRAFT_EOF'\\n---\\ndate: 2026-07-05\\nn: 1\\npillar: Technology & AI innovations\\nsource: evergreen\\nsource_date: 2026-07-05\\nstatus: pending\\n---\\n\\n𝗧𝗵𝗲 𝗔𝗜 𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝗿𝗮𝗰𝗲 𝗶𝘀𝗻'𝘁 𝗮𝗯𝗼𝘂𝘁 𝘄𝗵𝗼 𝗵𝗮𝘀 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗯𝗲𝘀𝘁 𝗺𝗼𝗱𝗲𝗹.\\n\\nIt's about who ships first.\\n\\nEvery week there's a new model. Smarter. Faster. Cheaper. And companies are frozen — waiting for the perfect stack, the perfect agent architecture, the perfect use case.\\n\\nMeanwhile, the winners are already in production with \\\"good enough\\\" agents solving real problems. They'll swap models later. The infrastructure stays. The learnings compound.\\n\\nThe gap between companies talking about AI and companies deploying AI is getting embarrassing. One group is writing strategy decks. The other is capturing market share.\\n\\nYour competitor's agent doesn't need to be perfect. It just needs to be live.\\n\\nWhat's stopping you from deploying your first agent this week?\\n\\n#AI #AIAgents #Innovation #Execution #UBOS\\nDRAFT_EOF\\n\\necho \\\"SAVED: Draft 1\\\"\\n\\n# Draft 2\\ncat > \\\"$PENDING_DIR/${TODAY}-draft-2.md\\\" << 'DRAFT_EOF'\\n---\\ndate: 2026-07-05\\nn: 2\\npillar: Business & entrepreneurship insights\\nsource: evergreen\\nsource_date: 2026-07-05\\nstatus: pending\\n---\\n\\n𝗬𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗻𝗲𝘁𝘄𝗼𝗿𝗸 𝗶𝘀 𝘆𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗯𝗲𝘀𝘁 𝗱𝗶𝘀𝘁𝗿𝗶𝗯𝘂𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻 𝗰𝗵𝗮𝗻𝗻𝗲𝗹.\\n\\nAnd you're ignoring it.\\n\\nFounders spend months chasing cold outreach, paid ads, and viral content. All valid. But the warmest leads are already in your phone — people who've seen you work, trust your judgment, and would take your call.\\n\\nThe problem? Most people only reach out when they need something. That's not networking. That's extracting.\\n\\nReal network building is:\\n- Sharing wins without asking\\n- Making intros without expecting returns\\n- Commenting thoughtfully on posts\\n- Showing up consistently in their feed\\n\\nBuild the relationship before you need the favor. By the time you launch, half the work is done.\\n\\nWho's one person in your network you should reconnect with this week?\\n\\n#Networking #FounderLife #Distribution #Relationships #Growth\\nDRAFT_EOF\\n\\necho \\\"SAVED: Draft 2\\\"\\n\\n# Draft 3\\ncat > \\\"$PENDING_DIR/${TODAY}-draft-3.md\\\" << 'DRAFT_EOF'\\n---\\ndate: 2026-07-05\\nn: 3\\npillar: Personal development & mindset\\nsource: evergreen\\nsource_date: 2026-07-05\\nstatus: pending\\n---\\n\\n𝗖𝗼𝗻𝘀𝗶𝘀𝘁𝗲𝗻𝗰𝘆 𝗯𝗲𝗮𝘁𝘀 𝗶𝗻𝘁𝗲𝗻𝘀𝗶𝘁𝘆 𝗲𝘃𝗲𝗿𝘆 𝘁𝗶𝗺𝗲.\\n\\nBut we keep betting on intensity.\\n\\nThe 14-hour sprint. The weekend warrior. The January 1st resolution. All gas, no steering. And then we burn out, disappear for months, and start over.\\n\\nThe people who win aren't the ones who go hardest. They're the ones who keep going.\\n\\n- Two posts a week, every week, beats ten posts one week and zero the next\\n- 30 minutes of focus daily beats three hours on Sunday\\n- One meaningful conversation a day beats ten networking events a year\\n\\nThe math is brutal: show up 1% better every day and you're 37x better in a year. Skip three months and you're at zero.\\n\\nYour brand, your skills, your network — they compound. But only if you keep adding to them.\\n\\nWhat's one thing you can commit to doing every day this month?\\n\\n#Mindset #Consistency #Growth #PersonalDevelopment #Habits\\nDRAFT_EOF\\n\\necho \\\"SAVED: Draft 3\\\"\\n\\n# Mark brief as sent\\ntouch \\\"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/$UID/pending/.brief-sent-$TODAY\\\"\\necho \\\"Brief marked as sent for $TODAY\\\"\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"vertex_ai/zai-org/glm-5-maas","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783232044135,"responseId":"LfZJapHKO4-bzPsPysWYsAU"}}
